Note on what I deliberately did NOT flag: the repeated wrapper prohibition (C10 first-word rule, X6 no-promise, prose-protocol class 7 requester-aimed words) and the triad emphasis (C11 + protocol class 1) overlap by design — these are the doctrine's most-failed behaviors and the redundancy is load-bearing reinforcement, not duplication. Likewise J3/C6/CAL7 (settled-means-settled) and E6/CAL2-3 (symptom-gone-mechanism-unverified) each add a distinct trigger or collision context, so they are not redundant. The self-check bullets restate pillars but serve as a distinct final-pass instrument, not a second statement of the rule.
